92. Apply the various steps involved to get cookie value using server-side scripting.
•	Create a cookie with setcookie().
•	Access it using $_COOKIE['cookieName'].
•	Always check isset() before accessing.
<?php
setcookie("user", "Kavya", time()+3600, "/"); // set
if (isset($_COOKIE['user'])) {
    echo "Cookie Value: " . $_COOKIE['user'];
} else {
    echo "Cookie not set yet!";
}
?>
